<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,261,2016]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,657,684]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Integumental papillae rounded or slightly extended, in some cases surrounded by a granulate area of additional small elevations (
<figureCitation box="[509,633,693,720]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1398,1423]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1378]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,174,1378]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–e. H. perreptans (MD 074a); a.–b. female and male Cx-I+II; c.–e. integument papillae in various views–note in e. the underlying hexagonal structure visible upper left; f.–k. H. megalonyx (MD 120a); f.–g. male and female Cx-I+II; h.–k. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613320" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613320/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Fig. 9 h 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[602,616,694,720]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
k
</figureCitation>
). Medial margin Cx-I smooth or with very inconspicuous projections near setae bases (
<figureCitation box="[350,466,729,756]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1398,1423]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1378]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,174,1378]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–e. H. perreptans (MD 074a); a.–b. female and male Cx-I+II; c.–e. integument papillae in various views–note in e. the underlying hexagonal structure visible upper left; f.–k. H. megalonyx (MD 120a); f.–g. male and female Cx-I+II; h.–k. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613320" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613320/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Fig. 9 f 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[435,449,730,756]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
g
</figureCitation>
). Cx-IV with a relatively long posteromedial apodeme, directed medially (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1423,729,756]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1718,1743]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,318,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,301,1699]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma, H. megalonyx, female (MD 120a). a. dorsal idiosoma; b. coxal and genital field; c. palp; d. III-L-4–6 posterior; e. IV-L-4–6 posterior." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613322/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 10 b</figureCitation>
). Swimming setae numbers (anterior/posterior) II-L-5, 0/0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[780,794,766,792]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
1; III-L-4, 0/5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[948,962,766,792]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
7; III-L-5, 0/4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1116,1130,766,792]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
8; IV-L-4, 3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1261,1275,766,792]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
7/5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1311,1325,766,792]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
8; IV-L-5, 0 [rarely 1 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[270,284,802,828]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
2–see remarks]/4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[477,491,802,828]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
6. Leg claws strongly enlarged–length (all legs) 40 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1068,1082,802,828]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
75 – 18 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1168,1182,802,828]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
31 % penultimate segment. Leg segments stout (e.g., L/H ratio I-L-5, 3.3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[726,740,838,864]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
3.9; II-L-5, 4.0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[907,921,838,864]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">–</emphasis>
4.6; III-L-5, 4.0 
